partysafe is released under Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike
4.0 International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0).

Full license text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/legalcode

Summary (not legal advice):
  - Share: copy and redistribute in any medium or format
  - Adapt: remix, transform, and build upon the material
  Under the following terms:
  - Attribution: you must give appropriate credit
  - NonCommercial: you may not use for commercial purposes
  - ShareAlike: if you remix or build upon the material, you must distribute
    your contributions under the same license

This license was chosen to match the license of the upstream TripSit drugs
dataset (https://github.com/TripSit/drugs), which this project incorporates.

Dual-licensing intent (to be finalized before public launch — see PLAN.md
ship gates):
  - The TripSit-derived data shipped under src/data/tripsit.json remains under
    CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 (required by upstream license).
  - Original mechanism content authored for this project (src/data/mechanisms.json)
    is intended to be dual-licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0 (without the NonCommercial
    clause) so harm-reduction organizations can redistribute freely.
  - Original UI code (everything in src/ outside data/) is intended to be
    dual-licensed under MIT.

  This dual-licensing structure will be finalized in writing, with attribution
  trails documented in ATTRIBUTION.md, before v1 public launch.
